  "text": "The hidden feature obtained at the 2nd layer is decoded by introducing the decoder part to the proposed model as shown below. Decoder facilitates the progressive dimensionality gain as opposed to the gradual dimension reduction via encoding layers. We choose the nodes for each hidden layer as shown in Fig. 4 . The pre-training for layer 1 and layer 2 is performed as described in Section 3.1. Once pre-trained weights are obtained (layer 1, layer 2 encoding weights), those encoding weights (W * l=1 , W * l=2 ) are used to tie the weights [CITATION_1] for the corresponding decoders as shown below:",
